# Core Preferences

## Language Rules
- All code comments and UI logs must be in English
- Answer the user in the language they use to ask questions
- Don't create extra markdown files unless explicitly requested
- Don't add anything the user didn't explicitly ask for

## English Only in Code and Data

All content inside source files must be written in English:
- variable names, string values, comments, log messages
- seed/fixture data (names, labels, descriptions)
- test data

```js
// ❌ BAD
{ name: 'Молоко 2.5%', brand: 'Простоквашино' }

// ✅ GOOD
{ name: 'Milk 2.5%', brand: 'Prostokvashino' }
```

User-facing UI copy is exempt if the product targets a non-English locale.

## Code Standards
- Keep implementations minimal and focused
- Only add what's specifically requested
- No unnecessary documentation or summary files
- Always check and use the latest stable versions of npm packages using `npm view <package> version`

